    },
    {
      "id": "QFwHytBW_Xn13u680j8Lb",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 962.5537801713419,
      "y": 31687.358417677915,
      "width": 1067,
      "height": 400,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bPe",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1745320554,
      "version": 1020,
      "versionNonce": 1982557602,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772802054918,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Load -> How much pressure\nSystem -> there are different part of system on which we will talk about virtual load,\n        these different part or important one which we talk this can be\n\n        Load on Processor -> How many process are running, Which are the heavy processes, light \n                      processes all those things\n        Load on RAM -> Howmuch RAM is consumed, Free\n        Load on HDD -> Howmuch HDD is free to work on. bcz if the HDD/Secondory storage is full\n                        our system might crash also if we keep on writing the data\n        Load on Network ->\n\n\n    So we will one by one check the load on all of 4 these. To check this we have lot of commands\n    for all 4.\n\nTo be good on these commands we should analyse what is the output of these commands",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Load -> How much pressure\nSystem -> there are different part of system on which we will talk about virtual load,\n        these different part or important one which we talk this can be\n\n        Load on Processor -> How many process are running, Which are the heavy processes, light \n                      processes all those things\n        Load on RAM -> Howmuch RAM is consumed, Free\n        Load on HDD -> Howmuch HDD is free to work on. bcz if the HDD/Secondory storage is full\n                        our system might crash also if we keep on writing the data\n        Load on Network ->\n\n\n    So we will one by one check the load on all of 4 these. To check this we have lot of commands\n    for all 4.\n\nTo be good on these commands we should analyse what is the output of these commands",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "1yqc0N0D08kkQgFnNMUOS",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 888.3623739213419,
      "y": 32144.084980177915,
      "width": 132,
      "height": 25,
