      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772802054918,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "How to see if any heavy process is running, how to find out, how we will stop that process?\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "How to see if any heavy process is running, how to find out, how we will stop that process?\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "ltY5pbB59qFpL1rPdVeYb",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 981.2647176713419,
      "y": 32524.510761427915,
      "width": 1067,
      "height": 850,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bPk",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1772581829,
      "version": 1921,
      "versionNonce": 637660450,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772802054918,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "ps -aux|grep python -> here we will get more than 1 process, we can get 2, 3, 4 but 1 of these \n        is of no use, this process itself , when this process runs, this will also be listed\n        in ps command\n\n    somewhere in running disk Python is also written, so this will also be mentioned but we are \n    not concerned about this because we have get the output and this is ended\n    \n    we will see one liine in whihc grep and other things will be mentioned we are not concerned\n    about this line, we are concerned about other lines.\n\n    ps -aux|grep python. here | symbol means take output of left side and pass it to write side\n        like we will do string pattern matching if there is python in output of ps -aux\n\n    grep is used for pattern matching\n\n    Now we know whihc Python process is running from there we can pick pid and from this pid\n    we will try to unalive that process or kill that process\n    \n    kill -9 pid -> it will kill the process with pid -> meaning of -9 is , if anything comming \n    after - then it will be a flag represents here we have to force kill.\n    \n    What is the meaning of force kill ->\n        there are two ways to kill a process one way is suppose in GUI we are closing tabs one\n        by one this will kill the process and other background related stuff like release memory \n        and all\n        but it will shut down the system this will close forcefully it is not guarantee related\n        memotry is released or not\n\n    ps -aux|less -> scrollable output in terminal\n    ps -aux|more -> scrollable output in terminal but only in downward direction\n    \n    less, more & grep command are general they are not related to ps command.\n\n    ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "ps -aux|grep python -> here we will get more than 1 process, we can get 2, 3, 4 but 1 of these \n        is of no use, this process itself , when this process runs, this will also be listed\n        in ps command\n\n    somewhere in running disk Python is also written, so this will also be mentioned but we are \n    not concerned about this because we have get the output and this is ended\n    \n    we will see one liine in whihc grep and other things will be mentioned we are not concerned\n    about this line, we are concerned about other lines.\n\n    ps -aux|grep python. here | symbol means take output of left side and pass it to write side\n        like we will do string pattern matching if there is python in output of ps -aux\n\n    grep is used for pattern matching\n\n    Now we know whihc Python process is running from there we can pick pid and from this pid\n    we will try to unalive that process or kill that process\n    \n    kill -9 pid -> it will kill the process with pid -> meaning of -9 is , if anything comming \n    after - then it will be a flag represents here we have to force kill.\n    \n    What is the meaning of force kill ->\n        there are two ways to kill a process one way is suppose in GUI we are closing tabs one\n        by one this will kill the process and other background related stuff like release memory \n        and all\n        but it will shut down the system this will close forcefully it is not guarantee related\n        memotry is released or not\n\n    ps -aux|less -> scrollable output in terminal\n    ps -aux|more -> scrollable output in terminal but only in downward direction\n    \n    less, more & grep command are general they are not related to ps command.\n\n    ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "0NrHXhlBcwb0L10VV8xLC",
