    {
      "id": "uBIlvutndSYIwo5AF1WTO",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1060.881905171342,
      "y": 41258.43654267791,
      "width": 1199,
      "height": 150,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bRt",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 720606168,
      "version": 685,
      "versionNonce": 2094997950,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772802054918,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Power OFF the ubuntu VM ->  go to settings > storage -> Add attachement -> Hardisk > create new disk -> vdi >\nnext > set memory as 1 GB -> finish -> attach ->  ok then boot the VM (49:00)\n\nfdisk -l -> now we will see one new Hardisk named /dev/sdb\n\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Power OFF the ubuntu VM ->  go to settings > storage -> Add attachement -> Hardisk > create new disk -> vdi >\nnext > set memory as 1 GB -> finish -> attach ->  ok then boot the VM (49:00)\n\nfdisk -l -> now we will see one new Hardisk named /dev/sdb\n\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "KeDyGTSnNbOdq3XsGy9Jx",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 932.0889364213419,
      "y": 41448.08498017791,
      "width": 352,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bRu",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 923530968,
      "version": 252,
      "versionNonce": 493576482,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772802054918,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Creating Partition in a Disk -> ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Creating Partition in a Disk -> ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "gkN891zHkRNyqBVZn6Df1",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1060.905342671342,
      "y": 41507.11623017791,
      "width": 1045,
      "height": 475,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bRv",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 328095912,
      "version": 998,
      "versionNonce": 1246771710,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772802054918,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "fdisk is not just a tool for listing, it also helps us to work on a disk also, work in a way\nthat we can create partitions and all that stuff so to do that rather than listing we will go\ninside our disk to do that we will do\n\nfdisk /dev/sdb\nm -> for printing the menu\nn -> new partition\np -> to create a primary partition , e for create a extended partition -> here we have chosen p\npartition  number just enter it will take defaul 1\nfirst sector -> just hit enter it will take default sector\nLast sector -> we can give either sector number or size for example if we want to create\n            100 MB partition then we can give +100M and hit enter\nnow partition is created of 100 MB size\nw -> for come out\n\nbydefault fdisk commands creates entry in partition table, but sometime due to some issue\nit may not create entry, to make sure entry is created we run command partprobe\npartprobe -> it will make sure partition entry is done on partition table for newly \n            created partition",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "fdisk is not just a tool for listing, it also helps us to work on a disk also, work in a way\nthat we can create partitions and all that stuff so to do that rather than listing we will go\ninside our disk to do that we will do\n\nfdisk /dev/sdb\nm -> for printing the menu\nn -> new partition\np -> to create a primary partition , e for create a extended partition -> here we have chosen p\npartition  number just enter it will take defaul 1\nfirst sector -> just hit enter it will take default sector\nLast sector -> we can give either sector number or size for example if we want to create\n            100 MB partition then we can give +100M and hit enter\nnow partition is created of 100 MB size\nw -> for come out\n\nbydefault fdisk commands creates entry in partition table, but sometime due to some issue\nit may not create entry, to make sure entry is created we run command partprobe\npartprobe -> it will make sure partition entry is done on partition table for newly \n            created partition",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "m-oJtcE-hpdAp4NSOohyp",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 920.4092489213419,
      "y": 42047.70998017791,
      "width": 550,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bRw",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 2035895256,
      "version": 68,
      "versionNonce": 1835461858,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772802054918,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "File system creation or Formating the Partition ->",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "File system creation or Formating the Partition ->",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "tGSIQvgoy-KLisBTn2r80",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1029.893623921342,
      "y": 42091.80763642791,
      "width": 946,
      "height": 375,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bRx",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 2099021480,
      "version": 1018,
      "versionNonce": 846481982,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772802054918,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Now we will try to make a file system in this file system. A way in which file can be\nstored or metadata can be created.\n\nNow to make file system command is mkfs\nmkfs. tab -> it will show all the file systems that we can choose. like ext2, ext3, ..\n\nmkfs.ext4 /dev/sda1 -> it will create file system in this partition /dev/sda1\n\nmkfs then double tab -> it will show all the command that mkfs supports\nmkfs. then double tab -> it will show all the things that we can attach with mkfs.\nda then double tab -> it will show date and dash\ndate then double tab -> it will show all the commands\n\nfuser -v /dev/sdb1 -> it will show user , PID, Access and command for this partition\nps -aux|grep fdisk -> it will show all the process having disk",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Now we will try to make a file system in this file system. A way in which file can be\nstored or metadata can be created.\n\nNow to make file system command is mkfs\nmkfs. tab -> it will show all the file systems that we can choose. like ext2, ext3, ..\n\nmkfs.ext4 /dev/sda1 -> it will create file system in this partition /dev/sda1\n\nmkfs then double tab -> it will show all the command that mkfs supports\nmkfs. then double tab -> it will show all the things that we can attach with mkfs.\nda then double tab -> it will show date and dash\ndate then double tab -> it will show all the commands\n\nfuser -v /dev/sdb1 -> it will show user , PID, Access and command for this partition\nps -aux|grep fdisk -> it will show all the process having disk",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "RGyT5l725RgYqnQl1yOPj",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1025.885811421342,
      "y": 42526.06154267791,
      "width": 440,
      "height": 175,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#e03131",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bS0",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 115623080,
      "version": 256,
      "versionNonce": 360382626,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772802054918,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Till now \nwe have picked a Disk\npartition banaya\npartition ki entry partition table me ki\nfile system banaya of type ext4 \n\nlast step is mounting",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Till now \nwe have picked a Disk\npartition banaya\npartition ki entry partition table me ki\nfile system banaya of type ext4 \n\nlast step is mounting",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "jqo4XpVArHfTTEWfaOweu",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 918.9561239213419,
      "y": 42778.19826142791,
      "width": 132,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bS1",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1489974488,
      "version": 45,
      "versionNonce": 1412190846,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772802054918,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Mounting -> ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Mounting -> ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "j_OhMItwMMvUwoOA4KQXM",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 977.7647176713419,
      "y": 42822.49904267791,
      "width": 1034,
      "height": 325,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bS5",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 480158168,
      "version": 901,
      "versionNonce": 290888802,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772802054918,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "For mounting what we need to do, we have existing OS, we are attaching a new partition in our\nexisting OS on a particular location, whenevery we will put the data in this location or\ndirectory it will go to that partition /dev/sdb1, we have /dev/sdb1 but we dont have directory\nso we need to create this directory\n\nTo create this directory \nmkdir drive -> this will create directory named and drive\nmount /dev/sda1 /root/drive -> this will mount /dev/sda1 partition to our repository drive\nTo check mounting works properly or not we will run command lsblk\nlsblk -> it will list all the block storage, about block storage we will talk later -> here\n        we can see our partition, where it is mounted also\n\nif we need to unmount use command umount /dev/sda1",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "For mounting what we need to do, we have existing OS, we are attaching a new partition in our\nexisting OS on a particular location, whenevery we will put the data in this location or\ndirectory it will go to that partition /dev/sdb1, we have /dev/sdb1 but we dont have directory\nso we need to create this directory\n\nTo create this directory \nmkdir drive -> this will create directory named and drive\nmount /dev/sda1 /root/drive -> this will mount /dev/sda1 partition to our repository drive\nTo check mounting works properly or not we will run command lsblk\nlsblk -> it will list all the block storage, about block storage we will talk later -> here\n        we can see our partition, where it is mounted also\n\nif we need to unmount use command umount /dev/sda1",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "LMkvskQory2mi8dymUINp",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 900.7529989213419,
      "y": 43171.42482392791,
      "width": 704,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
