    {
      "id": "q6TJ9LA1BBlN1Lu8NDF-Q",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1262.561592671342,
      "y": 45734.44044892791,
      "width": 671,
      "height": 150,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#e03131",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bSk",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 174914057,
      "version": 450,
      "versionNonce": 389611326,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772802054918,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Now if someone asking for storage, as per their need\nwe can carve out a chunk of storage that they need that\ncarving our a chunk is called a Logical Volume(LVM),\nwe are calling as Logical due to this is not a physical\nboundary of our HDD. This LVM is used for formatting and \nthen later on mounting. So this is how we get a larger space.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Now if someone asking for storage, as per their need\nwe can carve out a chunk of storage that they need that\ncarving our a chunk is called a Logical Volume(LVM),\nwe are calling as Logical due to this is not a physical\nboundary of our HDD. This LVM is used for formatting and \nthen later on mounting. So this is how we get a larger space.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
