    {
      "id": "fRI9mCo0uYRy0T_nZ-oUN",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 887.6670614213419,
      "y": 49095.78810517791,
      "width": 440,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bTZ",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1878430871,
      "version": 53,
      "versionNonce": 1475425342,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772802054918,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "There are lot of storage in terms of HDD",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "There are lot of storage in terms of HDD",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "NCqZKpK-4nDv8Hwxnii5G",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 972.4912801713419,
      "y": 49144.72560517791,
      "width": 1111,
      "height": 575,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bTa",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1415870937,
      "version": 1626,
      "versionNonce": 1108981410,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772802054918,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "File storage\nObject Storage\nBlock Storage\n\nfocus more on Object and block storage right now these are imp one\nwhen we talk about block storage, it is type of storage where we have complete command on \nwhat we can do with the disk\n\nGoogle Storage or Drive storage is OBject storage or Block Storage -> object storage bcz\n    we cant do partition, we dont have access to partition table or file system table.\n\nObject Storage how do we use it -> We just keep on puting things, we can make folders, we can\nput things inside folders, we can make folders inside folders and rather than accessing everything\none by one because it is not needed, everything we are puting there will be link to it and we can\njust use the item link directly rather than going structure by structure\nExample -> If someone ask us to upload resume or Google drive and share, we will upload and share the\nlink there is no need to share entire folder structure. So this works in a way that every object has\ntheir own direct access link. All the hieratchy is just a interface given to us to manage our storage\nmore easily, apart from that there is no purpose of it. We will work on Object storage when we will\nmove on Cloud\n\nRight now we are more focused in Block Storage -> In block storage, we can format, partition, mount\nbecuase we have access to those tables.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "File storage\nObject Storage\nBlock Storage\n\nfocus more on Object and block storage right now these are imp one\nwhen we talk about block storage, it is type of storage where we have complete command on \nwhat we can do with the disk\n\nGoogle Storage or Drive storage is OBject storage or Block Storage -> object storage bcz\n    we cant do partition, we dont have access to partition table or file system table.\n\nObject Storage how do we use it -> We just keep on puting things, we can make folders, we can\nput things inside folders, we can make folders inside folders and rather than accessing everything\none by one because it is not needed, everything we are puting there will be link to it and we can\njust use the item link directly rather than going structure by structure\nExample -> If someone ask us to upload resume or Google drive and share, we will upload and share the\nlink there is no need to share entire folder structure. So this works in a way that every object has\ntheir own direct access link. All the hieratchy is just a interface given to us to manage our storage\nmore easily, apart from that there is no purpose of it. We will work on Object storage when we will\nmove on Cloud\n\nRight now we are more focused in Block Storage -> In block storage, we can format, partition, mount\nbecuase we have access to those tables.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
