      "text": "Server",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "center",
      "verticalAlign": "middle",
      "containerId": "837iiU8swWgXTfBqFrCiz",
      "originalText": "Server",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "lH5f62ISt79z75NrfrQnJ",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1368.061592671342,
      "y": 50194.83107392791,
      "width": 627,
      "height": 225,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#e03131",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bTl",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 590053111,
      "version": 509,
      "versionNonce": 271764862,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772802054918,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "If it is giving web page it will be web server\nIf it is giving file it is FTP server, file server\nIf it is give time and date, It is time and date server\nIf it is allowing us to send mail, its a mail server\n    or a SMTP server\nIf it is providing IP address, it is a DHCP server\nIf it is providing domain name or domain name resolution\n    then its a DNS server\nBased on whatever it is serving it is that kind of server",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "If it is giving web page it will be web server\nIf it is giving file it is FTP server, file server\nIf it is give time and date, It is time and date server\nIf it is allowing us to send mail, its a mail server\n    or a SMTP server\nIf it is providing IP address, it is a DHCP server\nIf it is providing domain name or domain name resolution\n    then its a DNS server\nBased on whatever it is serving it is that kind of server",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "9npkIBh3Ba8I4IVQu8hBO",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 885.5069051713419,
      "y": 50684.89357392791,
      "width": 1100,
      "height": 125,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bTm",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1498024217,
      "version": 728,
      "versionNonce": 1531531618,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772802054918,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Between Client and server whenever we are trying to reach wired or wireless there is a medium always\nAnd mostly if we are not directly connected to that system via LAN connection then mostly there are\ndevices in the network, these devices can be our router or servers router and apart from that our\nlocal ISP, regional ISP, Zonal ISP, all the networks that we have to cross to reach to a particular\nsystem so these are the devices,these can be routers, switches, hubs, antennas, satelites anything.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Between Client and server whenever we are trying to reach wired or wireless there is a medium always\nAnd mostly if we are not directly connected to that system via LAN connection then mostly there are\ndevices in the network, these devices can be our router or servers router and apart from that our\nlocal ISP, regional ISP, Zonal ISP, all the networks that we have to cross to reach to a particular\nsystem so these are the devices,these can be routers, switches, hubs, antennas, satelites anything.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "P6bGtjHriNLny2FJNki-2",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 888.9639364213419,
      "y": 50859.33107392791,
      "width": 770,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bTn",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 2070384569,
      "version": 135,
      "versionNonce": 1438150078,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772802054918,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "If Someone ask please trubleshoot my laptot, Google.com is not opening",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "If Someone ask please trubleshoot my laptot, Google.com is not opening",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "hpYrcAS7YtJQE5iMIMBqu",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 944.2022176713419,
      "y": 50928.56154267791,
      "width": 1232,
      "height": 1150,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bTo",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1799387863,
      "version": 3742,
      "versionNonce": 1386009890,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772802054918,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "1.Generally first question will be were you able to open it before or never\n2. Are you able to open other websites? -> if only google.com is not workig other websites are working\nwhich tells us our gateway is configured properly, my router is configured properly, my router is able\nto get me to other websites. just google.com is the issue.\nBut if any website are not working most probably We have a issue with our router or our own system as well,\nso that be the case, So these kind of information we will try to collect, Once we collect the info, then\nwe move to the solution or we try to troubleshoot.\n3 are you writing correct google.com\n4 our network is up or not\n\nIf the correct domain is not working what we will try to check whether the wifi or internet is up or not\nin linux we can check using commands\nif up \nif down\nthese command are part of software that is slightly older software there is one more command whihc come for\nthis which is \nifconfig\n\nall these ifup, ifdown, ifcondif come under net tools we need to install that\napt install net-tools\n\nifconfig -> it will give name(enp0s8) of our NIC network interface card, the card that gives us internet \n        connection, if we will read detail of enp0s8 there will be a section of inet and in that inet we \n        get the ip address, if we are getting ip address over there, our net is on, if we are not getting\nIp address then our virtual machine network(net) is down.\nnet-tools is old comparatively. the newer command that we can use is\n\nip addr -> this will also show us the above detail like inet.\n            here we will get lo  > inet > 127.0.0.8 this addres is our localhost address or lo address or\n            home ip address.\n\nWhenever we communicate over network our system needs a ip address, IP address is needed so that two devices\non internet can be recognized uniquely by their unique ip address, Similarily when a system communicate to\nitself line one process communicate to other process, then also a particular IP address is needed at that time\nour localhose IP address is used.\nIt is more like whether our data move over internet or within own system. Data moves in form of packets, whether\nits a TCP packet or UDP packet but data moves in form of packets, Now to generate a packet, packet needs\nsomething over there that is called IP address, So when it is going within the system, at that time our\nIP address of our source or our destination is our localhost IP address.\n\nNow lets say it is not showing IP address, which means your internet is off, So we will try to turn ON our\ninternet, lets say we will use ifup command or any other command or mostly what we will do is because these\nare our cloud based system, So in our cloud we are not associated with the IP address we will try to \nassociate our system with the IP address And when we associate it with the IP address, when we are able to\ncommunicate with it over network so basically how our system will get IP address? this single question comes\nup with 5 6 different sub questions that are very famous interview question",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1.Generally first question will be were you able to open it before or never\n2. Are you able to open other websites? -> if only google.com is not workig other websites are working\nwhich tells us our gateway is configured properly, my router is configured properly, my router is able\nto get me to other websites. just google.com is the issue.\nBut if any website are not working most probably We have a issue with our router or our own system as well,\nso that be the case, So these kind of information we will try to collect, Once we collect the info, then\nwe move to the solution or we try to troubleshoot.\n3 are you writing correct google.com\n4 our network is up or not\n\nIf the correct domain is not working what we will try to check whether the wifi or internet is up or not\nin linux we can check using commands\nif up \nif down\nthese command are part of software that is slightly older software there is one more command whihc come for\nthis which is \nifconfig\n\nall these ifup, ifdown, ifcondif come under net tools we need to install that\napt install net-tools\n\nifconfig -> it will give name(enp0s8) of our NIC network interface card, the card that gives us internet \n        connection, if we will read detail of enp0s8 there will be a section of inet and in that inet we \n        get the ip address, if we are getting ip address over there, our net is on, if we are not getting\nIp address then our virtual machine network(net) is down.\nnet-tools is old comparatively. the newer command that we can use is\n\nip addr -> this will also show us the above detail like inet.\n            here we will get lo  > inet > 127.0.0.8 this addres is our localhost address or lo address or\n            home ip address.\n\nWhenever we communicate over network our system needs a ip address, IP address is needed so that two devices\non internet can be recognized uniquely by their unique ip address, Similarily when a system communicate to\nitself line one process communicate to other process, then also a particular IP address is needed at that time\nour localhose IP address is used.\nIt is more like whether our data move over internet or within own system. Data moves in form of packets, whether\nits a TCP packet or UDP packet but data moves in form of packets, Now to generate a packet, packet needs\nsomething over there that is called IP address, So when it is going within the system, at that time our\nIP address of our source or our destination is our localhost IP address.\n\nNow lets say it is not showing IP address, which means your internet is off, So we will try to turn ON our\ninternet, lets say we will use ifup command or any other command or mostly what we will do is because these\nare our cloud based system, So in our cloud we are not associated with the IP address we will try to \nassociate our system with the IP address And when we associate it with the IP address, when we are able to\ncommunicate with it over network so basically how our system will get IP address? this single question comes\nup with 5 6 different sub questions that are very famous interview question",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
