    {
      "id": "U7ulPGXRduwIBaH78fUTX",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1446.608467671342,
      "y": 52495.29201142791,
      "width": 374,
      "height": 125,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#e03131",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bUJ",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 497378296,
      "version": 202,
      "versionNonce": 270579966,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772802054919,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Existing network of systems\nall of them are connected to each \nother there is a mesh topology\nevery system is connected to every\nother system things like that",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Existing network of systems\nall of them are connected to each \nother there is a mesh topology\nevery system is connected to every\nother system things like that",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "S_FKEdH9Gy9XYxpS7nxbB",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 976.6983114213419,
      "y": 52369.52638642791,
      "width": 110,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#e03131",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bUK",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1770418824,
      "version": 117,
      "versionNonce": 169991650,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772802054919,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "New system",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "New system",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "ulW409YnjGv5EBdjITJmI",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1051.557686421342,
      "y": 52729.31544892791,
      "width": 924,
      "height": 175,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bUL",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 340512504,
      "version": 619,
      "versionNonce": 131918142,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772802054919,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Our new system is tries to connect to this existing network, So it will try to \nreach out to every system, and it will ask each and every system or it will send \nevery system a packet to receive an IP address and what is that packet asking\nthat packet is asking for IP, that packet is searching for IP.\nDHCP(Dynamic Host configuration protocal) server -> this server follows a particular\nprocess to give us IP address, this process called as DORA process to explore and\nfind the IP address",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Our new system is tries to connect to this existing network, So it will try to \nreach out to every system, and it will ask each and every system or it will send \nevery system a packet to receive an IP address and what is that packet asking\nthat packet is asking for IP, that packet is searching for IP.\nDHCP(Dynamic Host configuration protocal) server -> this server follows a particular\nprocess to give us IP address, this process called as DORA process to explore and\nfind the IP address",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "GV1V49UWDFvkWCJS4CzBd",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1044.069405171342,
      "y": 52948.35060517791,
      "width": 253,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bUM",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 2049643256,
      "version": 29,
      "versionNonce": 531616162,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772802054919,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "What is DORA Process ->",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "What is DORA Process ->",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "70MSUIqOc435h6c00vMAt",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1135.596748921342,
      "y": 52996.12794892791,
      "width": 1001,
      "height": 575,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bUN",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 422059144,
      "version": 1748,
      "versionNonce": 1361645950,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772802054919,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "IN this first step is called as discovery where in our system will send a message\nto every other system in the network asking who is the DHCP server. Or asking can\nyou give me the IP address\n\nSecond step is Offer -> in this step one of system will tell I am your DHCP\n\nthird step is request -> I want to get a Ip address, that DHCP server or our router\nor Hotspot or every such kind of system why they behave in a specific way or how they\nare able to make devices communicate, they are able to device communicate because\nthey are running DHCP inside them, DHCP basically allows them to create a table, that\ntable more looks like whoever comes they will notice the system lets say system1 system2\nand so on, and they will give unique ID to every system like IP1, IP2 and so one, Once\none IP is assigned to any system, they will not assign similar IP to another system, \nBecause in a network I am identifying each system with the unique IP address. Because we\nneed to send packet to that IP. Due to that DHCP make sure whoever is your router or mobile\nhotspot or anything it will make sure that only unique IPs are assigned to each system\n\nlast step is acknoledgement -> DHCP will acknowledge that yes IP is assigned you can start\nusing it, I have noted it over here like system x has ipx\n\n\nif 4 system are connected from our mobile hotspot then our hotspot is DHCP it will assign\nunique IP to all of them.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "IN this first step is called as discovery where in our system will send a message\nto every other system in the network asking who is the DHCP server. Or asking can\nyou give me the IP address\n\nSecond step is Offer -> in this step one of system will tell I am your DHCP\n\nthird step is request -> I want to get a Ip address, that DHCP server or our router\nor Hotspot or every such kind of system why they behave in a specific way or how they\nare able to make devices communicate, they are able to device communicate because\nthey are running DHCP inside them, DHCP basically allows them to create a table, that\ntable more looks like whoever comes they will notice the system lets say system1 system2\nand so on, and they will give unique ID to every system like IP1, IP2 and so one, Once\none IP is assigned to any system, they will not assign similar IP to another system, \nBecause in a network I am identifying each system with the unique IP address. Because we\nneed to send packet to that IP. Due to that DHCP make sure whoever is your router or mobile\nhotspot or anything it will make sure that only unique IPs are assigned to each system\n\nlast step is acknoledgement -> DHCP will acknowledge that yes IP is assigned you can start\nusing it, I have noted it over here like system x has ipx\n\n\nif 4 system are connected from our mobile hotspot then our hotspot is DHCP it will assign\nunique IP to all of them.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "3AgxWM9J6UNBj5wLGJiVf",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 958.2803426713419,
      "y": 52518.60451142791,
      "width": 407,
      "height": 75,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#e03131",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bUQ",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 697262328,
      "version": 286,
      "versionNonce": 2127121762,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772802054919,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Lets say this is our DHCP, or Hotspot\nor Router then this system will say\nI am your DHCP",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Lets say this is our DHCP, or Hotspot\nor Router then this system will say\nI am your DHCP",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
