    {
      "id": "S8fLnYEa_RcHRlUym8dZA",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 731.6351273708611,
      "y": 37137.73259608268,
      "width": 1001,
      "height": 425,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bVc",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1204255358,
      "version": 880,
      "versionNonce": 776671330,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772803391033,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "ip addr -> to check our system Ip addres, whether we are getting ip address or not.\n\nthen we will check for static ip or static route -> we can make our ip static\nDHCP -> this is a server that give us IP address\n\nFirewall -> rules 2 imp command -> ufw & fflush\n\ngateway(IP of our router) is set or not -> \nclear cache in browser and OS both then also it is not working whihc meand everything at\n    system level is fine and it means error or issue is somewhere outside system. All above\n    is within system.\n\n\nNow when we hit outside ->\n\n   what happen/ How our request reach to server -> \n        1 DNS resolution, Dont say DNS server, server in DNS itself",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "ip addr -> to check our system Ip addres, whether we are getting ip address or not.\n\nthen we will check for static ip or static route -> we can make our ip static\nDHCP -> this is a server that give us IP address\n\nFirewall -> rules 2 imp command -> ufw & fflush\n\ngateway(IP of our router) is set or not -> \nclear cache in browser and OS both then also it is not working whihc meand everything at\n    system level is fine and it means error or issue is somewhere outside system. All above\n    is within system.\n\n\nNow when we hit outside ->\n\n   what happen/ How our request reach to server -> \n        1 DNS resolution, Dont say DNS server, server in DNS itself",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
