    },
    {
      "id": "OQCMbodAQ-ZVG3fk4cOZz",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 905.5071819832453,
      "y": 38819.03832112596,
      "width": 1034,
      "height": 500,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bW6",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1309697470,
      "version": 1772,
      "versionNonce": 1590272702,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772805613132,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "IPv4 is older version of IP. basically it was 4 numbers of 8 bits each. each\nof them is separated by a period(.) symbol. since it is 8 bit each so each max number \nwould be when we set all as 1 255 and the min would be when we set all as 0, hence\nwe have 4 sets between 0 to 255.\n\nHistory -> jab internet bna naya naya, the people who were building this they thought\n    for communication obviously we need protocols, IP, stuff like that, So they created\n    IP, and at that time internet was widespread but not that much, because this was\nnot much widespread they thought this combination 255 * 255 ** 255 * 255, so it can\nserve many many systems globaly. this was not the problem till a long time like IP\naddress will be disappeared. Problem started when. IPs moves beyond devices like\ncomputers, PCs, mobiles, ACs, Washing Machines, TVs like literal every other thing, until\nand unless it was restricted till mobile phones and laptops and pcs it was fine, but when\nIOT comes then then spread became so huge. Nowaday we might not realize in our home how\nmany thing are there which are using IP.\nNow they might have not their public IP but where they are connecting that thing atleast\nto respond needs a public IP. sometimes devices need a public IP. So there are lot of things\nlike this, and because they need an IP address, in modern version of IP we have 6 sets instead\nof 4 and at the same time each of octet is also increased from 8 bits, now it is not octet.\nthis modern version is IPv6.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "IPv4 is older version of IP. basically it was 4 numbers of 8 bits each. each\nof them is separated by a period(.) symbol. since it is 8 bit each so each max number \nwould be when we set all as 1 255 and the min would be when we set all as 0, hence\nwe have 4 sets between 0 to 255.\n\nHistory -> jab internet bna naya naya, the people who were building this they thought\n    for communication obviously we need protocols, IP, stuff like that, So they created\n    IP, and at that time internet was widespread but not that much, because this was\nnot much widespread they thought this combination 255 * 255 ** 255 * 255, so it can\nserve many many systems globaly. this was not the problem till a long time like IP\naddress will be disappeared. Problem started when. IPs moves beyond devices like\ncomputers, PCs, mobiles, ACs, Washing Machines, TVs like literal every other thing, until\nand unless it was restricted till mobile phones and laptops and pcs it was fine, but when\nIOT comes then then spread became so huge. Nowaday we might not realize in our home how\nmany thing are there which are using IP.\nNow they might have not their public IP but where they are connecting that thing atleast\nto respond needs a public IP. sometimes devices need a public IP. So there are lot of things\nlike this, and because they need an IP address, in modern version of IP we have 6 sets instead\nof 4 and at the same time each of octet is also increased from 8 bits, now it is not octet.\nthis modern version is IPv6.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "VAQcdm3bkw7xK0AhfZtil",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 899.1119762655236,
      "y": 39368.03947751426,
      "width": 352,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
