      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772805646096,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Why we still talk about IPv4 -> ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Why we still talk about IPv4 -> ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "ulK572XE9ND3uv9I71gx6",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 967.9122596261104,
      "y": 39410.3722077994,
      "width": 1034,
      "height": 125,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bW8",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 762397282,
      "version": 544,
      "versionNonce": 236304162,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772806713198,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Because when we deal with servers or currently the servers that will be setting up for a very\nlong time, we are dealing with IPv4 only. IPv6 ka use IOT devices ke rare cases me ata h.\nFor now jitne bhi devices h world me, unko serve krne k liye IPv4 is enough. IPv6 is developed\nkeeping long future in mind. Because if internet has to survive then have to keep longer\nfuture in mind. For now IPv4 is more than enough even till our career will survive.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Because when we deal with servers or currently the servers that will be setting up for a very\nlong time, we are dealing with IPv4 only. IPv6 ka use IOT devices ke rare cases me ata h.\nFor now jitne bhi devices h world me, unko serve krne k liye IPv4 is enough. IPv6 is developed\nkeeping long future in mind. Because if internet has to survive then have to keep longer\nfuture in mind. For now IPv4 is more than enough even till our career will survive.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "M82LUwVmhXBJXivDc1YdU",
