      "index": "bXH",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 473276531,
      "version": 867,
      "versionNonce": 1190926493,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1773160618661,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "it will capture all the packets on that network card, and we can start\nreading one by one, we can read all data, that is going through router.\nThis dump can be save to specific type of file which is called .pcap file\n\nthere is one famous application in industry named WireShark whihc we can use\nto read the dumped data nicely, we can apply filter, we can look in a good\nway. \n\nWhy the name WireShark -> Due to long time back shark has cut the deep see\nwire and at the near hackers also attached there wire to the router, that\nwere constantly sending data to hackers, due to shark cut repair men go to\nrepair the wire and found this .",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "it will capture all the packets on that network card, and we can start\nreading one by one, we can read all data, that is going through router.\nThis dump can be save to specific type of file which is called .pcap file\n\nthere is one famous application in industry named WireShark whihc we can use\nto read the dumped data nicely, we can apply filter, we can look in a good\nway. \n\nWhy the name WireShark -> Due to long time back shark has cut the deep see\nwire and at the near hackers also attached there wire to the router, that\nwere constantly sending data to hackers, due to shark cut repair men go to\nrepair the wire and found this .",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
